secondary characters of primary Guild Members will be 15.<br>
<br>
2. If the prospective member has requested membership into the Guild, the Guild's <br>
Admission's Officer should contact the prospective member as soon as possible. The<br>
Admission's Officer will inform the prospective member of the process to become a <br>
member (i.e., point them to these rules).<br>
<br>
3. If a current Guild Member notices a person who would be an asset to the <br>
Guild, that member should talk with said person to determine their interest. <br>
If interested, the prospective Guild member should be directed to the Admission's Officer or to the Guild website for more information and the membership process.<br>
<br>
4. A guild applicant must have a primary sponsor from within the guild. That sponsor will be fully accountable for the prospective member's actions during the 30 day probationary period.<br>
<br>
5. Once the above are done, a prospective member will contact the Admission's Officer or the Guild Leader, informing them of their sponsor. The Admission's Offiicer and the Guild Leader will review the prospective member's application with the sponsor and other select officers and members, which shall vary at any given time.<br>
<br>
6. Upon the Admission's Officer's and Guild Leader's approval, the applicant will become a &quot;member initiate&quot; in the Guild on a 30 day &quot;trial&quot; basis. The officer who <br>
invited the member will then provide the new member the Members Only message <br>
board password and any other relevent information. This trial period is for <br>
the new member and the rest of the Guild to get to know each other further <br>
(group, raid, etc.) and establish their roots in the Guild. At the end of <br>
this 30 day period, the new member's membership will be reviewed by the Guild Leader and officers - and barring any issues, will become a full member of the Guild.<br>
<br>
7. Once a new member is added for their &quot;trial&quot; period, the officer that invited the member must contact the Admission's Officer informing him/her of the addition; including the initiates full Name (Character, not RL), Class, Race, and Level, so that they may be properly added to the Guild Roster. <p><img src="http://www.prexus.com/Aequus/jaansig2.jpg"></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ujaandir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jaandir</A> at: 7/10/01 6:15:11 am<br></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/faequusfrm10.showNextMessage?topicID=7.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/faequusfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/space/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/faequusfrm10.threadControl?topicID=7.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/space/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/faequusfrm10.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=7.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/faequusfrm10.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=7.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub14.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="aequusfrm10">Charter & Rules<option value="aequusgeneral">The Fountain<option value="aequusfrm6">The War Room<option value="aequusfrm7">The Town Gates<option value="aequusfrm5">Traders' Bazaar